Roasting with a touch of honey helps caramelize this creamy acorn squash. The sweetness from the squash and golden raisins pair perfectly with salty feta and nutty quinoa in this hearty grain salad.

== Roasted Squash ==

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Halve the @acorn squash{1}, scoop out the seeds, and cut into 1-inch slices. Strip the @thyme{1%sprig} leaves off the sprig. Drizzle with half the @honey{1%tablespoon}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, a pinch of @salt and @pepper and sprinkle thyme. Place on a #baking sheet{} and roast for ~{20-25%minutes}, until tender and caramelized.

== Quinoa ==

Heat 1 cup of @water{1%cup} in a #pot with the @veggie stock concentrate{1} and a pinch of @salt. Once boiling, add the @quinoa{1/2%cup} and simmer for ~{15%minutes}. Drain any excess liquid, return the pot, and cover.

== Mushroom & Quinoa Salad ==

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping white and green parts separate. Slice the @button mushrooms{4%ounce}.

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #pan over medium heat. Add the scallion whites and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Add the mushrooms and season with @salt and @pepper. Cook for ~{5%minutes}, until mushrooms are soft and browned.

In a #bowl, combine @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @white wine vinegar{1%tablespoon} and remaining @honey{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt and @pepper. Toss in the mushroom mixture, @golden raisins{1%ounce}, and quinoa. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Serve the quinoa-mushroom mixture with the roasted squash on top. Sprinkle with @feta cheese{1/4%cup} crumbles and scallion greens.